======================================================================
ANALYSIS 2: COMBINATORIAL IDENTITY SEARCH
======================================================================
56 = 2*C(7,5) + c3_vsets = 2*21 + 14 = 56
This would mean: c5_dir + 2*disj_33 = 2*C(n,n-2) + c3 for regular tournaments

n=6, score (2,2,2,3,3,3): c5_dir + 2*disj_33 = [12, 13, 14]
  (c5_dir, disj_33) pairs: [(6, 4, 14), (8, 2, 12), (11, 1, 13), (12, 1, 14)]

n=6, score (2, 2, 2, 2, 3, 4): c5_dir + 2*disj_33 = [9, 11]
  NOT constant (varies)

n=6, score (1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 3): c5_dir + 2*disj_33 = [9, 11]
  NOT constant (varies)

